    "title": "On August 21, 2024, Singapore's Ministry of Home Affairs and Minister for Home A...",
    "description": "On August 21, 2024, Singapore's Ministry of Home Affairs and Minister for Home Affairs and Law, K. Shanmugam, held a press conference to share details about a Bangladeshi national named Hamza Mohammad Amir\u2014better known as Amir Hamza. Amir Hamza had organized a religious gathering in Singapore without the required permit and used the event to make inflammatory remarks targeting people with opposing political and religious views. When the matter went to court, the prosecutor pointed out that his speech carried serious risks and could have fueled extremism and radicalization among the workers who were present. Shortly after the incident, Amir Hamza and his associate, Niamat Ullah, left Singapore, which prevented authorities from detaining them. Shanmugam and the ministry made it clear that such remarks have no place in Singapore and pose a real threat to national security. Ironically, the same Amir Hamza later secured nomination from Bangladesh Jamaat-e-Islami to run for the parliamentary election and ended up in as a Member of the Parliament. And ever since, he's been making reckless statements that seriously undermine the basic principles of democracy and social stability. He hasn't even spared veteran politicians who are undergoing critical medical treatment \u2014 absolutely disgraceful. The attached report is by CNA.",
